==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pathognomonic
<hw>Pa*thog`no*mon"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
skilled in judging of diseases; <grk>pa`qos</grk> a disease + <?/
skilled: cf. F. <ets>pathognomonique</ets>. See <er>Gnomic</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Specially or decisively characteristic of a
disease; indicating with certainty a disease; <as>as, a
<ex>pathognomonic</ex> symptom</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The true <qex>pathognomonic</qex> sign of love jealousy.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pathognomy</ent>⟦br⟧
